    "long_instructions": "### Assessment\r\n\r\nMake a song with an intro, verse, and chorus. All of your play blocks must be within functions. You can only use function calls, `play together`, and `repeat` blocks under When Run.\r\n\r\nThe intro should not contain any vocals, and then you must use at least 2 verse vocals and at least 2 chorus vocals.\r\n\r\nHere is an example of what your `when run` code could look like:\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/3abeb26093f627c7e20dac5e514b7f48-image-1745877347079.png)\r\n\r\nThis is an **Assessment** level, which means it covers the key parts of this lesson. Press the <i class=\"fa-clipboard-list fa-solid\"></i> Rubric button to see what it takes to fully complete this level!\r\n\r\nWhen you've finished the level, press the **Submit** button below! After you submit:\r\n- You won't be able to edit your code! If you need to make a change, you can press Unsubmit to make your edits and then submit again\r\n- Your teacher will be able to give you a score and feedback on your work",
